text: The Great Indonesia Movement Party (), better known as the Gerindra Party, is a nationalist, right-wing populist political party in Indonesia. It has been the third-largest party in the House of Representatives (DPR). It won 86 seats in the latest election. It is led by the former army general and the president-elect of Indonesia Prabowo Subianto. ==References== Category:2008 establishments in Asia Category:21st-century establishments in Indonesia Category:Political parties in Asia Category:Organizations based in Indonesia Category:Politics of Indonesia
